properties.name: Airport
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63Here\'s the airport we flew in and out of and then took the ferry across to the windward side of the bay where most everyone lived and all the work buildings were.

properties.name: Augustine Golf Club
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63 My mom worked here for a few years and I worked in the maintenance department during the summer between my sophomore and junior year.

properties.name: Beaufort, SC
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63I lived here from about the age of 1 year to 1 year and a half. My dad was stationed here shortly, but I do not recall for what reason. I know we lived on the beach, but other than that I do not remember anything about this place. Parris Island is also where my dad went to boot camp back in 1980.

properties.name: CO of the island's house.
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63This is where the Navy CO lived. I was able to go to his house once and it was huge.

properties.name: Cannery Row
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63Cannery Row is an awesome place to visit if you get the chance, as well as the Monterey Bay Aquarium.

properties.name: Catalina Island Boy Scout Camp
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63First Boy Scout Summer Camp I ever went to is located here. I believe this is the exact spot if I remember the camp set up correctly. It was 9 years or so ago.

properties.name: Citizen's Bank Park
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63Came here for a Phillies vs. the Braves game for my 19th birthday. Awesome looking ballpark.

properties.name: Cowpen Creek Road
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63My grandparents\' old trailer.

properties.name: Cutino Park
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63Played Pony Little League baseball and soccer here. The blue building is a Boys\' and Girls\' Club.

properties.name: Disney World
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63Came here when I was real little and as a freshman in high school with chorus. We sang at a Christmas lighting right here in this amphitheater by the world park area.

properties.name: Drit Track Area
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63We used to ride BMX bikes here, you can clearly see the trails in the image.

properties.name: Ferry
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63The detail is awesome as you can see the wake of the ferry outlined in the water.

properties.name: Georgetown Waterfront Near Kennedy Center
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63Smoked a good cigar here once. Not a smoker, but I\'ll smoke a cigar once a year if it\'s a good one. Georgetown is a good looking place, wish I had pictures.

properties.name: Grand Canyon
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63Looked right over this ridge. Visited here on our move from Cuba to California. This place looks awesome in the satellite image. The change in elevation and shadowing from the sun is awesome.

properties.name: HP Pavilion at San Jose
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63525 W. Santa Clara St., San Jose, CA, United StatesThe Shark Tank. Saw my first and only NHL game here with the Sharks vs. Rangers. There is a really good Mongolian BBQ right near the arena.

properties.name: Hoover Dam
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63Visited here on our move from Cuba to Cali. This place looks great in person and on a satellite image.

properties.name: Kennedy Center
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63Saw the opera La Traviata here my junior year of high school with my Madrigal group.

properties.name: Medical Center East Incorporated
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63 50 Medical Park Dr E, Birmingham, AL

properties.name: Metz Park
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63Wow they\'ve got this thing labeled. Used to play Bronco Little League baseball here.

properties.name: Minefields
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63I don\'t know the exact location of all the minefields on the islands, but my dad was OIC (Officer in charge) of Minefield Maintenance (MFM - "Death From Below") when we lived here. He was also OIC when they took out the last known mine on the U.S. portion of the island. We\'ve got pictures, but they\'re in boxes moving from VA to FL and not on a digital camera. Wish I could show you some.

properties.name: Monterey Little League Baseball Park
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63Funny it\'s only called ball park. I played All-Star\'s here as well as the Bronco Little League World Series. Nice looking park for just little league.

properties.name: Monterey Peninsula Country Club
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63My mom worked here while we lived in Seaside/Monterey. 50,000 to become a member, not including yearly dues. That\'s crazy.

properties.name: Mt. Tamalpais
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63Can\'t find the peak here like I could looking at Google Earth (which has a larger viewing range), but we climbed this mountain on a Boy Scout camping trip. Also got to visit John Muir woods and see some redwood trees.

properties.name: Paintball Course
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63They built this when I first moved to Cuba and my friends and I used to play here every weekend.

properties.name: Pebble Beach
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63  I was able to see a few AT&T Pro-Am\'s here back when everyone played in them as well as the 2000 U.S. Open. I\'ve got pictures of Tiger Woods back at home. Also able to see Spyglass and Poppy Hills golf courses. The 18th hole at Pebble Beach is more beautiful than pictures or TV can show.

properties.name: RFK Stadium
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63I\'ve been here for several Nationals games, mostly against my Braves. Would like to come up and see D.C. United play at some point.

properties.name: Shea Stadium
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63In my only trip to NYC, I came to see the Braves play the Mets. Even rode the famous 7 train and boy was that interesting. NYC is definitely not a place for just anyone, including myself. Nice to see, but not to live there.

properties.name: Shopping Center
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63 Shopping center we used to shop at as well as the mall in Monterey.

properties.name: Stone Mountain
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63This is a great marvel to visit. Saw it on my move from Cuba to California.

properties.name: The Beach
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63  This is the beach we used to swim at, which is right next to the U.S./Cuban border. I also noticed that the detainment camp they built for terrorists is not far down the beach. Glad I\'m not swimming there anymore.

properties.name: The Pentagon
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63My dad worked here for about six months while I was in high school. Fortunately it was after 9/11 took place.

properties.name: The Strip
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63Visited The Strip on our trip from Cuba to Cali. Too bad I wasn\'t old enough to check out the inside of most casinos, but the kid attractions were just as good, including MGM Grand. We stayed at Key Largo Hotel and Casino.

properties.name: Toronto
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63During a 9 day tour with the Maranatha Touring Choir, we stopped in Toronto to sing at an all black Baptist Church. Was a unique experience and on the tour, each night we spend with a family, usually 2 people per. It was a great experience and I wish I would have had the time to do it 10-12th grade like I did my freshman year. We got to visit Niagara Falls as well during the trip.

properties.name: Turner Field
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63I\'ve been here several times to see my Braves play and have gone through Atlanta too many times to visit my grandparents in Birmingham.

properties.name: Verizon Center (formerly MCI Center)
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63Came here for a Kanye West and Usher concert. Wizards and Capitals play here, but I\'ve never been to see them play, although I almost came up once for a Caps game.

properties.name: Washington Monument
properties.description: Posted by Jtaylo63I\'ve been to D.C. too many times, but this thing looks awesome on this satellite image. I love the military monuments the most though.
